# Entity Filing Resolver

Use this table to determine where a new entity belongs.

| Signal type | Primary home | Test |
|---|---|---|
| Person | `people/` | Subject is a specific human |
| Company/org | `companies/` | Subject is an organization |
| Active workstream | `projects/` | Has deliverables + timeline |
| Scheduled event | `meetings/` | Has date + participants |
| Pre-execution concept | `ideas/` | No timeline yet |
| Recurring observation | `patterns/` | 3+ occurrences |
| One-off learning | `insights/` | Single occurrence, worth remembering |
| Choice made | `decisions/` | Committed action with tradeoffs |

## Conflict Resolution
- If entity fits two categories, use the **more specific** one (e.g., person > company employee)
- meetings/ pages may reference people/ and projects/ but the meeting itself lives in meetings/
- When an idea gains a timeline and deliverables, migrate from ideas/ → projects/
- When a pattern is acted upon, create a decisions/ entry and link back
